 {"indices": [4378, 4382], "text": "MOD"}, {"indices": [4387, 4392], "text": "TSEM"}, {"indices": [4480, 4485], "text": "COHR"}, {"indices": [4633, 4636], "text": "MU"}], "urls": [], "user_mentions": []}, "quoted_tweet": {"type": "tweet", "id": "2048209995377045682", "url": "https://x.com/wey_how12640/status/2048209995377045682", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/wey_how12640/status/2048209995377045682", "text": "April 24, 2026 - Process, not PnL\n$LITE $SNDK $MU $MRVL $CIEN $BE $GEV $CLS $AAOI $NBIS $Q $TSEM $TSLA $ONDS $IPGP $COHR $CCJ\n\nA) Use of Leverage & Missing Opportunities\n\nI did quite some deleveraging as the week closed with $MU hitting $500 and $SNDK hitting $1000. \n\nBeing too heavy in overall portfolio (was 170% in) did tie up my mental flexibility to be more proactive and aggressive in new ideas e.g. those \"CPU theme\" of $AMD $ARM $INTC) and what else. \n\nBut I also realise that I can't have my cake and eat it too, I probably have chosen to go bigger in names which I am more comfortable with instead of opening smaller starters in new names, and the end result might probably the same if not better.\n\nBut for sure this CPU theme will be on my watchlist.\n\nB) Positions/ Theme at a glance\n\nStrategy is mainly AI theme, where bottlenecks are at.\n\n3 primary positions $LITE, $SNDK, $MU take up more than 50% weight, appropriately trimmed some before their coming earnings where applicable. $LITE is AI optical while $SNDK and $MU are AI memory.\n\nThe rest are still AI optical heavy, in line with my belief/ chart. $MRVL & $CIEN  take up another 16%, and $AAOI $TSEM $COHR $IPGP another 16%.\n\nAI power $BE $GEV $CCJ 16%.\n\nAI compute/ Semi related $NBIS $CLS $Q another 16%.\n\nNew starters, 3% each, which haven't gone anywhere\n$ONDS, $TSLA.\n\n(all % are approximate, I don't do exact).\n\nC) Going forward\n\nThis current generation is probably the least patient of all, chasing for constant actions and instant gratifications with much shorter timeframes, as though sitting still through a pullback or simply let profits run is a sin.\n\nPersonally content with doing nothing, yet flexible enough to do anything as things develop.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 1, "replyCount": 1, "likeCount": 36, "quoteCount": 1, "viewCount": 8546, "createdAt": "Sun Apr 26 01:18:11 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 17, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2048209995377045682", "displayTextRange": [0, 282], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "wey_how12640", "url": "https://x.com/wey_how12640", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/wey_how12640", "id": "1707559719215489024", "name": "Wey How", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1849391659106385920/SV3ICsLW_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1707559719215489024/1729764316", "description": "", "location": "Hong Kong SAR", "followers": 6233, "following": 322, "status": "", "canDm": false, "canMediaTag": true, "createdAt": "Fri Sep 29 00:55:44 +0000 2023", "entities": {"description": {"urls": []}, "url": {}}, "fastFollowersCount": 0, "favouritesCount": 11570, "hasCustomTimelines": true, "isTranslator": false, "mediaCount": 4357, "statusesCount": 11941, "withheldInCountries": [], "affiliatesHighlightedLabel": {}, "possiblySensitive": false, "pinnedTweetIds": ["1767016951392637090"], "profile_bio": {"description": "A Trend Following Theme Investor with a learning-driven approach to trading. Process over Outcome, Context over Patterns, Stocks over Setups, EC over Ego.", "entities": {"description": {}}}, "isAutomated": false, "automatedBy": null}, "extendedEntities": {}, "card": null, "place": {}, "entities": {"hashtags": [], "symbols": [{"indices": [34, 39], "text": "LITE"}, {"indices": [40, 45], "text": "SNDK"}, {"indices": [46, 49], "text": "MU"}, {"indices": [50, 55